which is totally unnecessary and causes confusion so do not
print an error message in this case.. Here is the corrected version:

	int ret;

	ret = recv_data(pev);
	if (ret < 0 && ret != DNS_EAI_ALLDONE && ret != -ENOENT) {
		NET_ERR("DNS recv error (%d)", ret);
	}
}

